# Firestore Patterns

## Schema
```
invites/{inviteId}
  ├── hostId, location, dateTime (Timestamp), heading, hostName, templateType, createdAt
  ├── gifts/{giftId}     — itemName, link, isClaimed, claimedBy
  └── rsvps/{rsvpId}     — guestName, pax, timestamp
users/{uid}              — uid, email
```

## Type-Safe Reads — `withConverter`
```ts
// ❌ const data = snap.data() as Invite;
// ✅ Use converter — types enforced at SDK level
const ref = doc(db, COLLECTIONS.INVITES, id).withConverter(inviteConverter);
const invite = (await getDoc(ref)).data(); // Invite | undefined
```

## Avoiding Composite Indexes
Filter in Firestore, sort in JS:
```ts
const snap = await getDocs(query(collection(db, "invites"), where("hostId", "==", uid)));
return snap.docs.map(d => d.data()).sort((a, b) => b.createdAt.getTime() - a.createdAt.getTime());
```

## Pagination (mandatory for lists)
```ts
const page = query(col, where("hostId", "==", uid), limit(20));
// Next page: startAfter(lastDoc)
```

## Count Queries
```ts
// ❌ getDocs then .size
// ✅ getCountFromServer(collection(db, `invites/${id}/rsvps`))
```

## Transactions for Race-Prone Writes
Gift claiming MUST use `runTransaction` to prevent double-claims. Never `updateDoc` on shared mutable fields.

## Listener Cleanup
Every `onSnapshot` must return an unsubscribe function cleaned up in `useEffect` return.

## Auth Pattern
`useAuth()` from `src/lib/auth-context.tsx`. Dashboard routes redirect to `/` if unauthenticated. Always show a skeleton during loading — no flash of content.

## Collection Constants
Never hardcode collection names. Use `COLLECTIONS.INVITES`, etc.
